
[1]critically

   CRITICALLY, adv.

   1. In a critical manner; with nice discernment of truth or falsehood,
   propriety or impropriety; with nice scrutiny; accurately; exactly; as,
   to examine evidence critically; to observe critically.

   2. At the crisis; at the exact time.

   3. In a critical situation, place or condition, so as to command the
   crisis; as a town critically situated.
